Section 1:
132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST SPECIAL SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1245
H.P. 820 House of Representatives, March 25, 2025
Waterfronts
Reference to the Committee on Housing and Economic Development suggested and
ordered printed.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative RIELLY of Westbrook.
Cosponsored by Senator TEPLER of Sagadahoc and
Representatives: ANKELES of Brunswick, GERE of Kennebunkport, GOLEK of Harpswell,
STOVER of Boothbay, STROUT of Harrington, Senator: DUSON of Cumberland.
Printed on recycled paper
1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 5 MRSA §3207 is enacted to read:
3 §3207. Working Waterfront Information Campaign Fund
4 The Working Waterfront Information Campaign Fund, referred to in this section as
5 "the fund," is established. Balances in the fund may not lapse and must be carried forward
6 and used for the purposes of this section. The fund is administered by the office, and the
7 office may accept and deposit in the fund money from private and public sources. In
8 carrying out the purposes of the fund, the office shall work with the Department of
9 Economic and Community Development, Office of Tourism; coastal municipal and
10 regional governments; and organizations and coalitions that have experience advocating
11 for the protection and preservation of working waterfronts in the State and experience
12 working with persons who use working waterfronts in the State. In collaboration with the
13 entities listed in this section, the office shall use the fund in the production of working
14 waterfront information campaigns, including the design and implementation of an online
15 and direct mail information campaign targeting tourists and new residents in coastal and
16 island communities, to provide information about what working waterfronts are, who uses
17 working waterfronts and opportunities to protect and preserve working waterfronts. As
18 used in this section, "working waterfront" means a parcel of land abutting water subject to
19 tidal influence or land located in the intertidal zone that is used primarily or predominantly
20 to provide access to or support the conduct of commercial fishing and marine activities.
21 SUMMARY
2222 This bill establishes the Working Waterfront Information Campaign Fund, which is
2233 administered by the Maine Office of Community Affairs. The office is directed to work
2244 with the Department of Economic and Community Development, Office of Tourism;
2255 coastal municipal and regional governments; and organizations and coalitions that have
2266 experience advocating for the protection and preservation of working waterfronts in the
2277 State and experience working with persons who use working waterfronts in the State. In
2288 collaboration with those entities, the office is directed to produce working waterfront
2299 information campaigns.
